  Police in Adamawa State have arrested an 18-year-old boy for allegedly defiling a four-year-old girl. The teenager took advantage of the minor being a close neighbour living with her grandmother, police said. “The Adamawa State Police Command, on 4/6/2021, apprehended  an 18-year-old suspect for sexually assaulting a four-year-old baby,” the command said in a statement by spokesman Suleiman Nguroje.  According to Nguroje, “The suspect, Ayuba Hamza, a resident of Jabbi Lamba village in Girei, took the advantage of the baby following the separation of her parents that brought her under the care and custody of her grandmother. “The grandmother who caught the suspect in the act, cried and attracted the attention of some neighbours.” He said the state Commissioner of Police, Aliyu Adamu Alhaji, had directed “discreet investigations into the case as the victim is under medical attention.”